We have also seen that there are other strong grounds for believing that Secundus was not relegated to the background, and that the very phrase in c. 399 ipsam quin immo curam et diligentis stili anxietatem contrariam experimur is preeminently appropriate to the individua] whom Quintilian had characterised as being ‘infinitae tamen curae!
